A 38-year-old suspect has been arrested for dealing in dagga after it was found loaded at the back of the truck that was destined for Bloemfontein from Lesotho. According to police spokesperson, Phumelelo Dlamini, the suspect was stopped and searched in Ficksburg.He said the dagga has a street value of more than R9million. “The total bags of dagga were later established to be 607 and stacked behind the truck,” said Dlamini.He added that the suspect is expected to appear at the Ficksburg Magistrates Court on charges of possession and dealing in drugs.